Welcome to Gotham Pickleball!

\
I am a former collegiate tennis player and pro skateboarder and a surfer. - movement is my medicine. I was introduced to pickleball in 2019 and, given my tennis background, took to it immediately. I was instrumental in helping organize with the Los Angeles Parks & Recreation Department convert spaces to pickleball courts across LA County. I moved to NYC in 2022, and have enjoyed being a part of the growing scene here. I’m a medic on my off days and volunteer with the Central Park Medical Unit.

\
My goal is to help you elevate your game!

\
Stats: 5.0+ CERTIFIED DUPR COACH

\
2024 Certified RPPk & DUPR COACH + Master Instructor

2024 RPO Certified

Sponsored Team Player @Gearbox_pickleball

\
Gold Medalist 2023 APP Women Doubles

Bronze Medalist 2023 APP Mixed Doubles

Silver Medalist 2023 1010 Wins Women Doubles

MLP Champion 2023 - Dink Daddies X Brooklyn Aces | NYC Pickleball

Silver Medalist 2022 APP Women Doubles

\
LETS HAVE SOME FUN!

\
Come [Join My DUPR Coaching Team](https://link.myjourneypickleball.com/UxjI7frimOb)

Simply download the My DUPR Coach app using my unique link and create an account.

\
This opportunity allows me to provide you with exclusive access to high-tech pickleball skills technology and the ability to generate the first-ever Provisional DUPR!

\
As one of my valued players, YOU have the chance to be among the first to utilize these exciting tools for improving your pickleball skills. We’ll have opportunities to work together through film analysis, comprehensive skills assessments, in-person events, and much more!

\

\
 \n 

\

Experience

I’ve been playing pickleball for nearly four years and began coaching in September 2023. Since then, I’ve coached at multiple facilities across New York City, helping players of all ages and backgrounds develop a love for the game. Whether on the Upper East Side where I first picked up a paddle, or on courts throughout the boroughs, I bring passion and energy to every session.

 \n 

Coaching Style

My coaching style is passionate, energetic, and focused on the fundamentals. I believe in helping players build strong foundational skills while ensuring they’re having fun every step of the way. I specialize in working with “Never-Evers,” beginners, and intermediate-level players who want to grow their game in a supportive and upbeat environment.

 \n 

Certifications

• Level 1 Certified Coach – Pickleball Coaching International (PCI)

• Level 1 Certified Coach – Racket Professional Organization (RPO)

 \n 

Skill Level

skill level: 4.0+

 \n 

Additional Info

I started playing pickleball in Carl Schurz Park on Manhattan’s Upper East Side, and the journey since then has been incredible. I love being on court—whether I’m playing, teaching, or just talking pickleball. I’ve met amazing people through this sport, and I’m excited to help more players experience the same. Outside of pickleball, I’m a proud dad, husband, and avid snowboarder. If you’re looking to elevate your game and have a great time doing it, I’d love to work with you.

 \n 

Contact Info:

📧 Email: NeilDiamondNYC@gmail.com

📱 Phone: 917-520-7551

📸 Instagram: __[@Pickleball_JEWELA](https://www.instagram.com/Pickleball_JEWELA)__
